00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:44,949
♪

254
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:48,244
Oh, this is truly magnificent.

255
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:50,455
I got her!

256
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:52,832
(cheering)

257
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,792
♪

258
00:13:54,792 --> 00:13:58,046
Don't get in my way!

259
00:13:58,046 --> 00:14:00,631
(rumbling)

260
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:05,803
♪

261
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:09,223
(snarling)

262
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:11,392
Oh my God, is she...

263
00:14:11,392 --> 00:14:17,315
♪

264
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:20,359
(screaming)

265
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:22,487
(laughing)

266
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:25,990
And that's because you
fools attempted witchcraft.

267
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:29,786
Looks like you guys
summoned the real demon.

268
00:14:29,786 --> 00:14:31,829
Just kidding!

269
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:34,832
All right then, let me try.

270
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:39,504
Young lady, I'd like to
have a word with you.

271
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:41,672
Okay.

272
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:44,926
‐Hey, wait just a second!
‐No way!

273
00:14:46,761 --> 00:14:49,514
Damn it, nothing there, but
it still looks suspicious.

274
00:14:49,514 --> 00:14:52,183
Now I need to catch
up with Yuki.

275
00:14:52,183 --> 00:14:54,227
Hey, stop!

276
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:57,313
♪

277
00:14:57,313 --> 00:15:00,566
What the hell is that up there?

278
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:03,861
Takenaga!

279
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:08,032
It's only me, I came
to pick you up.

280
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:12,036
So that means...

281
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:15,373
Hello again, and
good evening to you.

282
00:15:15,373 --> 00:15:18,209
Yeah, good evening to you too.

283
00:15:18,209 --> 00:15:20,545
‐Hey, did you wait long?
‐Ranmaru?

284
00:15:20,545 --> 00:15:23,339
When I explained what
happened, the only one

285
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:25,424
who actually offered
to help us was‐‐

286
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,218
Tamao, and here we are!

287
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:30,388
You were so reckless, don't do
something so dangerous again!

288
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:34,183
I was really worried
about you, super worried!

289
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:35,852
‐You big dummy!
‐I'm really sorry,

290
00:15:35,852 --> 00:15:38,855
‐but we have to find Yuki.
‐Ranmaru explained everything.

291
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:41,566
‐So let us go.
‐Thanks very much.

292
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:45,903
Of course, it's not bother at
all for my precious friends.

293
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:48,322
By the way, as far as
troops and artillery,

294
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:50,741
what do you suppose we
ought to have at the ready?

295
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:52,994
‐Driver?
‐Yes ma'am, Lady Tamao.

296
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:54,912
For starters, we
have special forces

297
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:57,290
and an army of 100
infantry soldiers

298
00:15:57,290 --> 00:16:00,376
equipped with machine guns
and rocket launchers.

299
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:05,131
We have air, land, and
sea completely covered.

300
00:16:05,131 --> 00:16:07,592
Is our attack satellite
operation all set?

301
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:09,927
We expect it will
take another 15 minutes

302
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:11,262
to lock on to the target.

303
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:13,598
I must apologize,
we're still new at this.

304
00:16:13,598 --> 00:16:17,310
‐I think you did great.
‐You didn't have to go this far.

305
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:20,271
(cooing)

306
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:25,651
‐Sunako?
‐Wait a damn minute!

307
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,653
Kyohei!

308
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,322
Where the hell did you take her?

309
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:32,533
If you'll agree to come back
to our arcade, we'll tell you.

310
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,619
It'll be just like
the good old days.

311
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:38,039
Buy 10 cartons of tofu and
get a free photo of Takano.

312
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:39,540
(together)
Yes, I'll buy it!

313
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,959
Buy a melon and a matsutake
mushroom and you'll get

314
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:44,962
‐Takano's phone number!
‐Yes, I'll buy it!

315
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:48,299
Buy a snapper and a crab and
we'll tell you Takano's address.

316
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:51,052
(together)
Yes, I'll buy it!

317
00:16:51,052 --> 00:16:54,055
If you came back to our arcade,
people would come from not only

318
00:16:54,055 --> 00:16:57,016
the neighborhood, but from
all over the country as well.

319
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,644
Your presence will
save our businesses.

320
00:16:59,644 --> 00:17:02,188
Don't give me that crap,
who's fault do you think it is

321
00:17:02,188 --> 00:17:03,689
I had to leave
in the first place?

322
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:06,817
I'll never go back there!

323
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:11,405
‐Come back to us.
‐Come back to us.

324
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:15,201
Kyohei, I'm coming
to save you‐‐ow.

325
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:19,455
Come back to us,
come back to us.

326
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:23,709
Come back to us,
come back to us.

327
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:27,922
Come back to us,
come back to us.

328
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:30,633
(shrill screaming)

329
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:33,511
(phone ringing)

330
00:17:33,511 --> 00:17:36,180
(doorbell chiming)

331
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:41,227
♪

332
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:44,438
That noise, I can't
take it anymore!

333
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:48,943
Please stop, someone
please make it stop!

334
00:17:48,943 --> 00:17:50,486
Come back to us.

335
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:54,031
So how can I go back
when I don't have a home?

336
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:56,325
Kyohei?

337
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:59,620
Kyohei, I'm sorry.

338
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,457
Your mother is tired of this.

339
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:06,127
Because the truth
is that my parents

340
00:18:06,127 --> 00:18:08,879
are much happier without me.

341
00:18:08,879 --> 00:18:11,090
What a nice family.

342
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:13,092
That's a lot better

343
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:16,387
than just being cool.

344
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:19,015
‐No, Kyohei!
‐What the hell?

345
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:21,392
(grunting)

346
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:23,811
Kyohei's a member of our family,

347
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:26,814
and we're not gonna
let you have him!

348
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:29,233
‐Yuki?
‐Catch that little kid!

349
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:30,901
(together)
Yes, sir!

350
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:33,029
(screaming)

351
00:18:33,029 --> 00:18:36,198
Yuki, grab an axe and
come cut these ropes!

352
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:38,451
Never mind, just run!

353
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:40,286
Bakers are best at baking,

354
00:18:40,286 --> 00:18:42,747
and butchers are
best at butchering.

355
00:18:42,747 --> 00:18:44,915
That's true and I'm very scared.

356
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:48,502
Run for it, Yuki, I'll
be fine, don't worry!

357
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:54,175
♪

358
00:18:54,175 --> 00:18:58,179
I won't let any of you
lay a finger on Kyohei!

359
00:18:58,179 --> 00:19:01,766
(together)
Aw!

360
00:19:01,766 --> 00:19:04,477
Calm down, it was
just a water drop!

361
00:19:04,477 --> 00:19:06,562
(together)
Aw!

362
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:09,607
(whimpering)

363
00:19:09,607 --> 00:19:11,859
Right, now bring it on!

364
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:13,986
So adorable.

365
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:16,947
It feels kinda
like we're bullying.

366
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:19,784
After all, we're not
really bad people.

367
00:19:19,784 --> 00:19:23,287
Here's a box‐cutter,
don't cut yourself, okay?

368
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,498
Oh!

369
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:27,708
Come on, this way!

370
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,877
Yuki, slow down!

371
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:36,175
♪

372
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:39,220
(tires screeching)

373
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:40,513
There's that van!

374
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,474
It's the one that was
used to kidnap Kyohei!

375
00:19:43,474 --> 00:19:45,559
‐Yuki!
‐Hey!

376
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:48,521
Takenaga, Ranmaru!

377
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,773
So what are Noi and the
rich girl doing here?

378
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:52,692
When you're in trouble,
there's real strength

379
00:19:52,692 --> 00:19:55,069
‐in numbers, right?
‐Right.

380
00:19:55,069 --> 00:19:57,154
Yuki, how are you, are you hurt?

381
00:19:57,154 --> 00:20:00,408
You scraped the
top of your nose.

382
00:20:00,408 --> 00:20:03,202
I'm just fine,
I mean, after all,

383
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,913
I rescued Kyohei!

384
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:07,748
‐Huh, no way!
‐Huh, no way!

385
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:10,334
(laughing and clapping)

386
00:20:10,334 --> 00:20:12,336
Ahem!

387
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:14,964
They followed us!

388
00:20:14,964 --> 00:20:16,507
So go ahead and bring it!

389
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:19,677
‐I mean, please don't.
‐They're the witchcraft users.

390
00:20:19,677 --> 00:20:22,471
‐Driver?
‐Yes, Lady Tamao.

391
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:25,474
Driver launcher!

392
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:27,935
Stop, we see how
big it is, so stop!

393
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:32,565
‐Driver.
‐As you wish, Lady Tamao.

394
00:20:32,565 --> 00:20:35,359
Ahem, we'll let
you go for today.

395
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:38,154
Well that's some nerve,
you kidnapped them!

396
00:20:38,154 --> 00:20:41,323
We were defeated, we
lost to your cuteness.

397
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:44,410
‐To my cuteness?
‐For his sake,

398
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:47,621
we're going to let you
off this time, Takano,

399
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:49,749
but don't fool yourself.

400
00:20:49,749 --> 00:20:52,251
That doesn't mean
we've given up.

401
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:55,379
Whatever, just realize what
you're doing is wrong!

402
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:57,631
(rooster crowing)

403
00:20:57,631 --> 00:20:59,717
Oh, it's morning!

404
00:20:59,717 --> 00:21:02,928
(mixed remarks)

405
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:08,017
♪

406
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:11,270
So anyway, what did he mean,
"lost to your cuteness"?

407
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:13,147
Did you dress up
like a girl again?

408
00:21:13,147 --> 00:21:16,192
Seriously, your cuteness
works on everyone, Yuki.

409
00:21:16,192 --> 00:21:20,404
‐Your cuteness is invincible.
‐That's truly amazing cuteness.

410
00:21:20,404 --> 00:21:22,615
I'm so totally lame.

411
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:25,117
♪

412
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:27,661
You saved me, thanks, Yuki.

413
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:31,248
♪

414
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:34,543
(laughing)

415
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:37,671
♪

416
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:40,341
All right then,
let's go home now.

417
00:21:40,341 --> 00:21:42,802
All that worrying
made me really hungry.

418
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:44,428
Why don't we stop at
a family restaurant?

419
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:47,014
‐I agree!
‐Would it be all right

420
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:49,642
‐if I asked you a question?
‐What is it?

421
00:21:49,642 --> 00:21:52,061
Do you know where
Miss Sunako went to?

422
00:21:52,061 --> 00:21:55,606
(together)
What?

423
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:58,150
She isn't here?

424
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:05,699
♪

425
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:08,452
I think you oughta
ask her about Kyohei.

426
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:10,120
I don't want to ask.

427
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:13,749
I never want to deal with a life
controlled by Kyohei again.

428
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:16,210
Never again, never!

429
00:22:16,210 --> 00:23:40,002
♪

430
00:23:44,048 --> 00:23:46,216
‐Good day to you.
‐Lady Tamao, it appears

431
00:23:46,216 --> 00:23:48,802
that your precious friend,
Miss Sunako has been kidnapped.

432
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:50,721
‐Driver!
‐In this case, I suppose

433
00:23:50,721 --> 00:23:52,723
rescuing her would be
the right thing to do.

434
00:23:52,723 --> 00:23:54,934
‐Driver!
‐Yes, Lady Tamao?

435
00:23:54,934 --> 00:23:56,894
‐Giddy up!
‐Yes, Lady Tamao.

436
00:23:56,894 --> 00:24:00,731
Next time on The Wallflower:
The Eye of the Storm Comes Home.

437
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:03,108
‐Driver bazooka!
‐Giddy up!

